rComments: Brough a thrully insightful perspective, anti **** feminism to global world view
Probably the worst prof i have ever had. her exams and midterms are horrible and the way she lectures can put anyone to sleep.
Hijin's leaving, too bad cause she's the most thought provoking prof out there. She's different and a bit quirky. Totally hot too.

this class was simply awesome. the discussions were (mostly) great and hijin does a great job of letting it move along naturally but maintaining control. it's a great class to have the things you believe in challenged in an amazingly constructive way. hijin rocks!!!

Hijin is very knowledgeable and thought provoking. She doesn't choose run of the mill material at all. I love this professor because we have great discussions on the topics she selects. She is also very helpful and cares about students. She gives decent grades too. Can't find a bad thing to say about her!
This is one of my favorite profs at UofT. Prof. Park is extremely helpful and grades papers/exams fairly. Great class!
Excellent command of course material; thoughtful, well-reasoned lectures; challenging; fair; always available.

She clearly knows what she's talking about, it's the delivery of the lecture that's lacking.  Don't think she started a single lecture on time, most at least 20-minutes late.  Still, with more experience, lectures might improve.  She is approachable, friendly, and helpful.
Absolutely ridiculous, extremely biased and at times even nauseating to listen to, maybe she should try teaching her students rather than forcing her own leftist ideologies onto them

Ms. Park's lectures are very sophisticated, demonstrating a nuanced and profound understanding of the material; her subtle & thorough analysis is inspiring. Although her class is challenging (especially for lazy undergrads) it is very rewarding. You can tell she really cares about the work.
i find her thought provoking and her lectures leave an impact.
